ENTRY       EC 3.4.21.7                 Enzyme
NAME        plasmin;
            fibrinase;
            fibrinolysin;
            actase;
            serum tryptase;
            thrombolysin
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Serine endopeptidases
REACTION    Preferential cleavage: Lys! > Arg!; higher selectivity than trypsin. Converts fibrin into soluble products
COMMENT     Formed from plasminogen by proteolysis which results in multiple forms of the active plasmin. In peptidase family S1 (trypsin family).
HISTORY     EC 3.4.21.7 created 1961 as EC 3.4.4.14, transferred 1972 to EC 3.4.21.7
